Titolo: Ken's Labyrinth

Anno: 1993

Descrizione: Ken's Labyrinth is a first-person shooter MS-DOS game, released in 1993 by Ken Silverman through his Advanced Systems and later by Epic MegaGames. It was fully coded by Ken Silverman, who later went on to design the Build engine that was used for rendering a first-person viewpoint in 3D Realms's Duke Nukem 3D (1996) and most recently in Ion Fury (2019). It consists of three episodes, the first of which was released as shareware.